        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 9:44PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 943 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
West Blocton, or 9 miles north of Centreville, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Vance, Woodstock, West Blocton, North Bibb, Green Pond, Hebron, and
Marvel.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
